WEBVTT

00:00:00.033 --> 00:00:03.136
Class Prez, want to catch a movie
with me and Mao Mao?

00:00:03.136 --> 00:00:05.171
I heard that action movie
is super thrilling and touching.

00:00:05.171 --> 00:00:07.807
- It's a must-watch!
- Aren't you playing basketball with us?

00:00:07.807 --> 00:00:09.942
- What basketball?
- Why aren't you inviting us to the movie?

00:00:09.942 --> 00:00:10.143
-

00:00:10.143 --> 00:00:14.112
Hang on, aren't you staying back
to decorate the classroom with me?

00:00:14.112 --> 00:00:14.414
-

00:00:14.414 --> 00:00:15.815
- Come to the movie!
- Play basketball with us!

00:00:15.815 --> 00:00:17.083
We already bought everything.

00:00:17.083 --> 00:00:19.085
- The movie!
- How about this?

00:00:19.085 --> 00:00:21.920
From 5:30 to 6:30,
I'll decorate the classroom with you.

00:00:21.920 --> 00:00:22.122
-

00:00:22.122 --> 00:00:24.124
From 6:30 to 7:30, I'll play with you guys.

00:00:24.124 --> 00:00:25.492
After that, I'll watch the movie
with you bunch.

00:00:25.492 --> 00:00:27.827
- Deal?
- Of course!

00:00:27.827 --> 00:00:29.229
And it's Saturday tomorrow.

00:00:29.229 --> 00:00:31.231
We can hang out past midnight.

00:00:31.231 --> 00:00:34.334
Have supper, too! Supper!

00:00:34.334 --> 00:00:35.635
I bet you're all thirsty.

00:00:35.635 --> 00:00:37.037
I'll treat you to drinks, cool?

00:00:37.037 --> 00:00:38.671
Sure.

00:00:38.671 --> 00:00:40.874
Thanks, Class Prez.

00:00:40.874 --> 00:00:42.042
You're the best.

00:00:42.042 --> 00:00:44.482
- What movie are we watching?
- What do you want to watch?

00:01:08.548 --> 00:01:10.570
Chen Hao Wei.

00:01:10.570 --> 00:01:12.973
I want to watch the movie with you, too.

00:01:12.973 --> 00:01:14.240
How do you know about that?

00:01:14.240 --> 00:01:16.109
I'm in the group chat with Mao Mao.

00:01:16.109 --> 00:01:18.211
But they didn't say anything
about the place and time.

00:01:18.211 --> 00:01:22.112
- I can tell you.
- Hey, text me.

00:01:22.112 --> 00:01:22.515
-

00:01:22.515 --> 00:01:24.107
I'll add your contact.

00:01:30.723 --> 00:01:31.991
I have a question.

00:01:31.991 --> 00:01:34.499
What's that person in your class called...

00:01:37.397 --> 00:01:39.732
He's a wallflower. Super weird guy.

00:01:39.732 --> 00:01:40.065
-

00:01:40.065 --> 00:01:42.902
His results are always last,
but he's trying to stand out.

00:01:42.902 --> 00:01:45.428
But what's his name?

00:01:47.807 --> 00:01:49.142
He Xiang Yong.

00:01:49.142 --> 00:01:50.477
He Xiang Yong.

00:01:50.477 --> 00:01:51.578
Thanks.

00:01:51.578 --> 00:01:53.079
I sent you a sticker, check it.

00:01:53.079 --> 00:01:54.505
Sure.

00:02:56.643 --> 00:03:00.445
Why have you come to Starry Islet
to look for him?

00:03:02.882 --> 00:03:05.478
- Actually, I...
- Who did this?

00:03:12.825 --> 00:03:15.069
Who made this bitter gourd black tea?

00:03:16.896 --> 00:03:18.631
Didn't you say she didn't bring anyone along?

00:03:18.631 --> 00:03:20.274
Who are you...

00:03:22.402 --> 00:03:26.639
Only He Xiang Yong knows I drink
bittergourd tea when I'm stuck.

00:03:26.639 --> 00:03:28.309
Why do you know?

00:03:34.948 --> 00:03:38.553
I also get anxiety.

00:03:39.485 --> 00:03:41.412
When I'm anxious, I also...

00:03:43.923 --> 00:03:46.991
I read it in a book.
Bittergourd black tea helps reduce anxiety.

00:03:46.991 --> 00:03:47.327
-

00:03:47.327 --> 00:03:50.499
So, I made some for you.

00:03:51.664 --> 00:03:53.188
I get you.

00:03:56.236 --> 00:03:58.137
So, you're Xi Xi?

00:03:58.137 --> 00:03:59.537
No.

00:04:01.274 --> 00:04:02.709
You're wearing...

00:04:02.709 --> 00:04:04.081
What's wrong?

00:04:05.278 --> 00:04:06.846
Did all of you see?

00:04:06.846 --> 00:04:08.314
Calm down.

00:04:08.314 --> 00:04:11.249
No, we didn't see anything.
Chen Hao Wei, hear me out.

00:04:11.249 --> 00:04:11.517
-

00:04:11.517 --> 00:04:15.555
Did you see a furious, infuriated lady?

00:04:15.555 --> 00:04:17.423
- Yeah.
- That's right.

00:04:17.423 --> 00:04:17.655
-

00:04:17.655 --> 00:04:21.594
What about a lady running about
with checkered panties?

00:04:21.594 --> 00:04:24.395
- Well, she...
- Look at me.

00:04:24.395 --> 00:04:24.631
-

00:04:24.631 --> 00:04:25.865
One more question.

00:04:25.865 --> 00:04:28.134
Did you see a lady without makeup
and totally disheveled

00:04:28.134 --> 00:04:31.148
but she looks just like Xi Xi?

00:04:32.939 --> 00:04:35.241
- Nope.
- Great.

00:04:35.241 --> 00:04:37.525
- I saw nothing!
- Perfect, you didn't see anyone.

00:04:39.345 --> 00:04:43.383
I think Xi Xi will be hungry later.

00:04:43.383 --> 00:04:46.085
Let's see if the kitchen has ingredients
to cook something for her.

00:04:46.085 --> 00:04:47.453
Great idea.

00:04:47.453 --> 00:04:48.855
Yeah, come on.

00:04:48.855 --> 00:04:50.922
I bought groceries. So...

00:04:50.922 --> 00:04:51.269
-

00:04:52.091 --> 00:04:53.622
Well...

00:04:55.328 --> 00:04:57.796
It's okay. I'm fine.

00:04:57.796 --> 00:04:58.019
-

00:04:59.832 --> 00:05:02.268
- She really is Xi Xi?
- Yeah.

00:05:02.268 --> 00:05:05.014
How long does she take
to leave the house on a regular day?

00:05:05.014 --> 00:05:07.113
[Ladder Steps]

00:05:07.113 --> 00:05:12.078
[Focus! Stop slacking!]

00:05:12.078 --> 00:05:13.680
Strange.

00:05:13.680 --> 00:05:16.067
I'm connected to the internet.

00:05:18.786 --> 00:05:20.632
[Focus! Stop slacking!]
[Hama-chan]

00:05:20.632 --> 00:05:20.841
-

00:05:24.984 --> 00:05:27.794
He's gone missing for days.

00:05:27.794 --> 00:05:30.076
He doesn't even come for shaved ice.

00:05:33.160 --> 00:05:34.967
[Angelamama]

00:05:37.170 --> 00:05:38.571
Hey.

00:05:38.571 --> 00:05:41.438
- Hey.
- Hey.

00:05:43.209 --> 00:05:45.316
I thought my phone was broken.

00:05:46.913 --> 00:05:49.382
I really can't figure you out.

00:05:49.382 --> 00:05:52.051
Which one's really broken?
Your phone or your head?

00:05:52.051 --> 00:05:54.687
You've been on your phone the whole morning.

00:05:54.687 --> 00:05:56.322
I wasn't.

00:05:56.322 --> 00:05:58.824
I just think my phone's lost its signal.

00:05:58.824 --> 00:06:01.019
No signal? Let me see.

00:06:01.961 --> 00:06:03.696
It's super strong, great signal.

00:06:03.696 --> 00:06:05.953
Fine, I get it.

00:06:06.933 --> 00:06:08.768
You're waiting for a call.

00:06:08.768 --> 00:06:11.902
No, I'm not.
I'm not waiting for texts either.

00:06:11.902 --> 00:06:12.022
-

00:06:13.940 --> 00:06:15.308
Didn't I tell you?

00:06:15.308 --> 00:06:19.113
You can't wait for customers to appear.

00:06:19.113 --> 00:06:22.115
You have to invite them over.

00:06:22.115 --> 00:06:25.284
It's the same with everything else.

00:06:25.284 --> 00:06:28.755
In life, you have to be more proactive.

00:06:28.755 --> 00:06:30.507
Are you very proactive?

00:06:32.058 --> 00:06:33.693
Whenever Xiao Hai's here,

00:06:33.693 --> 00:06:36.295
wasn't I very enthusiastic,
greeting him with a huge smile?

00:06:36.295 --> 00:06:38.732
Yes, sure.

00:06:39.699 --> 00:06:42.168
Recently, he hasn't been coming here.

00:06:42.168 --> 00:06:45.102
Who cares? He can live his own life.

00:06:45.102 --> 00:06:45.343
-

00:06:46.339 --> 00:06:48.408
Oh, I guess so.

00:06:48.408 --> 00:06:50.410
Did you two have a fight?

00:06:50.410 --> 00:06:52.503
D-Don't be so gossipy!

00:06:52.503 --> 00:06:55.947
- Get to work.
- I am working.

00:07:07.493 --> 00:07:10.329
Fine, I spread the word.

00:07:10.329 --> 00:07:12.346
I know.

00:07:13.132 --> 00:07:14.967
Your phone isn't broken.

00:07:14.967 --> 00:07:17.036
The taro balls are going
to be ruined, get over here!

00:07:17.036 --> 00:07:20.670
All right. I'm also about to break apart!

00:07:20.670 --> 00:07:20.924
-

00:07:31.350 --> 00:07:35.388
Only He Xiang Yong knows I drink
bittergourd tea when I'm stuck.

00:07:35.388 --> 00:07:36.556
Why do you know?

00:07:36.556 --> 00:07:38.002
Did I?

00:07:39.725 --> 00:07:42.622
1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.

00:07:43.463 --> 00:07:46.098
1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.

00:07:46.098 --> 00:07:48.367
1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.

00:07:48.367 --> 00:07:50.885
What caterpillars?

00:08:52.798 --> 00:08:54.103
Not asleep yet?

00:08:54.934 --> 00:08:56.243
I'm reading.

00:09:02.441 --> 00:09:04.575
- You left it here?
- Yep, it's my collection.

00:09:04.575 --> 00:09:04.844
-

00:09:04.844 --> 00:09:06.535
Why is it there?

00:09:15.888 --> 00:09:18.656
- Aren't you scared?
- What's so scary about a caterpillar?

00:09:18.656 --> 00:09:18.969
-

00:09:20.526 --> 00:09:22.242
Turn the lights off later.

00:09:32.872 --> 00:09:34.636
Why are you shivering?

00:09:36.309 --> 00:09:38.614
I'm cold from taking a cold shower.

00:10:15.014 --> 00:10:16.350
It's fake.

00:10:16.975 --> 00:10:18.416
It's fake.

00:10:24.790 --> 00:10:26.435
You can do it.

00:10:28.961 --> 00:10:30.596
It's fake.

00:10:30.596 --> 00:10:32.469
Nothing scary about it.

00:10:35.067 --> 00:10:37.216
But Chen Hao Wei is real.

00:10:37.837 --> 00:10:39.665
Really annoying.

00:10:41.140 --> 00:10:43.042
I'm such an idiot.

00:10:43.042 --> 00:10:45.244
What am I thinking?

00:10:45.244 --> 00:10:47.524
How can they be the same person?

00:10:52.251 --> 00:10:54.031
Watch your step.

00:11:08.901 --> 00:11:10.736
We're glad to have you on Starry Islet!

00:11:10.736 --> 00:11:12.598
Hope you had fun here!

00:11:26.218 --> 00:11:28.320
Did you forget something?

00:11:28.320 --> 00:11:30.513
"A Promise Beyond Time".

00:11:32.425 --> 00:11:33.969
What promise?

00:11:34.927 --> 00:11:38.431
The publishing house like such simple titles.

00:11:38.431 --> 00:11:42.968
But my editor prefers the titles
we brainstormed together.

00:11:42.968 --> 00:11:46.338
"Sweets, Seeds, Prophecy Diaries."

00:11:46.338 --> 00:11:47.373
She's super famous.

00:11:47.373 --> 00:11:48.774
"Hunter's Gentle Vacation,"

00:11:48.774 --> 00:11:52.242
"Sweets, Seeds, Prophecy Diaries,"
"Goddess Zandeer" are all her works.

00:11:52.242 --> 00:11:53.879
I love her comics.

00:11:53.879 --> 00:11:56.096
You're my idol.

00:12:03.089 --> 00:12:04.290
You're He Xiang Yong, aren't you?

00:12:04.290 --> 00:12:06.391
Yes. No!

00:12:06.391 --> 00:12:06.592
-

00:12:07.293 --> 00:12:09.328
I'm his friend.

00:12:09.328 --> 00:12:12.231
He mentioned that book to me before.

00:12:12.231 --> 00:12:14.534
I heard that it's a top seller. Congrats.

00:12:16.302 --> 00:12:18.137
No matter how one's appearance changes,

00:12:18.137 --> 00:12:20.606
their soul remains the same.

00:12:20.606 --> 00:12:25.557
You even know about secrets
I'll never reveal to anyone.

00:12:29.815 --> 00:12:31.831
What happened to you?

00:12:32.551 --> 00:12:35.011
Why do you look different?

00:12:55.274 --> 00:12:57.524
I don't know how to explain this...

00:12:58.144 --> 00:13:02.441
But... do you believe that shooting stars
can make wishes come true?

00:13:03.849 --> 00:13:05.918
Very interesting.

00:13:05.918 --> 00:13:07.953
Tell me more.

00:13:07.953 --> 00:13:11.056
I just made a wish without much thought.

00:13:11.056 --> 00:13:12.958
Who knew it'd come true?

00:13:12.958 --> 00:13:15.859
I woke up the next day and nobody recognizes me now.

00:13:15.859 --> 00:13:15.995
-

00:13:15.995 --> 00:13:17.999
I'm also trying to figure things out.

00:13:18.631 --> 00:13:22.591
So, you can't revert to your old self?

00:13:23.602 --> 00:13:25.538
Am I any different?

00:13:25.538 --> 00:13:28.453
I feel like I'm still my old self.

00:13:29.074 --> 00:13:31.447
How was I at the publishing house?

00:13:36.341 --> 00:13:39.577
Wait, but how did you recognize me?

00:13:46.892 --> 00:13:48.492
A gift.

00:13:50.696 --> 00:13:51.892
Thanks.

00:13:52.643 --> 00:13:54.011
Thank you.

00:13:56.304 --> 00:13:58.905
I don't like chatting.

00:13:58.905 --> 00:14:01.707
Being my editor is tough.

00:14:01.707 --> 00:14:04.034
But you never complained.

00:14:05.544 --> 00:14:08.280
You're just like Starry Islet.

00:14:08.280 --> 00:14:12.032
Filled with energy and warmth.

00:14:13.152 --> 00:14:16.121
Starry Islet deserves more attention.

00:14:16.121 --> 00:14:17.489
You.

00:14:17.489 --> 00:14:19.558
He Xiang Yong.

00:14:19.558 --> 00:14:21.985
You also deserve to shine bright.

00:14:30.035 --> 00:14:31.629
You don't have to send me all the way.

00:14:32.738 --> 00:14:34.136
Bye.

00:14:53.622 --> 00:14:59.185
[Embrace your broken past self
to become a better you]

00:15:17.950 --> 00:15:20.486
Zhong.

00:15:20.486 --> 00:15:22.488
Have you seen Xiao Hai lately?

00:15:22.488 --> 00:15:24.156
- Who?
- Xiao Hai.

00:15:24.156 --> 00:15:25.724
Have you seen him?

00:15:25.724 --> 00:15:27.760
He hasn't come back
after taking a few days of leave.

00:15:27.760 --> 00:15:29.585
I'm looking for him.

00:15:32.765 --> 00:15:34.430
Him? Taking days off?

00:15:36.035 --> 00:15:37.623
That's impossible.

00:15:49.348 --> 00:15:50.549
De.

00:15:50.549 --> 00:15:52.551
We're here for the beer.

00:15:52.551 --> 00:15:53.753
Xiang Yong.

00:15:53.753 --> 00:15:55.653
Xiang Yong. Candy.

00:15:55.653 --> 00:15:55.754
-

00:15:55.754 --> 00:15:57.890
Your favourite watermelon candy.

00:16:02.795 --> 00:16:05.517
Hong, you've got the wrong person.

00:16:15.941 --> 00:16:17.144
Hong.

00:16:17.876 --> 00:16:19.964
You think he's Xiang Yong, too?

00:16:22.481 --> 00:16:24.182
Plum candy. Yours.

00:16:24.182 --> 00:16:24.483
-

00:16:24.483 --> 00:16:26.051
Not now, thanks. Answer me first.

00:16:26.051 --> 00:16:28.495
You think he's Xiang Yong too, right?

00:16:31.623 --> 00:16:33.069
Thanks, Hong.

00:16:38.964 --> 00:16:42.122
Aren't the shooting stars
on Starry Islet super gorgeous?

00:16:44.169 --> 00:16:46.171
They're magical, too.

00:16:46.171 --> 00:16:48.621
They can make wishes come true.

00:16:50.909 --> 00:16:56.018
Do you know what happens
after wishes come true?

00:16:59.651 --> 00:17:01.490
People will...

00:17:09.361 --> 00:17:11.063
But love will remain.

00:17:11.063 --> 00:17:12.680
You sure you don't want watermelon candy?

00:17:24.743 --> 00:17:25.778
Thanks, madam.

00:17:25.778 --> 00:17:28.572
Thanks. Come back again.

00:17:30.883 --> 00:17:33.485
Oh, Mr. Li!

00:17:33.485 --> 00:17:35.354
What grand mission are you on?

00:17:35.354 --> 00:17:37.022
Why don't I see you around?

00:17:37.022 --> 00:17:39.425
Nah, it's just that someone's missing.

00:17:39.425 --> 00:17:43.662
- Can't find them.
- Gone missing? Do we need to call the police?

00:17:43.662 --> 00:17:44.763
I...

00:17:44.763 --> 00:17:47.266
What if... he doesn't want to see me?

00:17:47.266 --> 00:17:49.501
Won't that be so embarrassing?

00:17:49.501 --> 00:17:50.769
Ugh, I'm annoyed when he's around.

00:17:50.769 --> 00:17:51.937
And I'm annoyed when he's gone.

00:17:52.905 --> 00:17:54.239
If you could choose...

00:17:54.239 --> 00:17:57.109
Would you rather see him or not see him?

00:17:57.109 --> 00:17:58.911
See him, of course.

00:17:58.911 --> 00:18:01.613
Congrats, you like him.

00:18:01.613 --> 00:18:03.048
No way, I can't be in love with Hama-chan.

00:18:03.048 --> 00:18:04.416
Impossible.

00:18:04.416 --> 00:18:05.818
Hama-chan.

00:18:07.152 --> 00:18:11.957
This isn't a fight, it's a tiff.

00:18:11.957 --> 00:18:13.125
Wait, Mom! You've misunderstood.

00:18:13.125 --> 00:18:16.361
I want to see him
because I want to beat him up.

00:18:16.361 --> 00:18:17.930
I don't like him.

00:18:17.930 --> 00:18:20.164
Fine, then go and beat him up.
He's waiting for you at home.

00:18:20.164 --> 00:18:20.432
-

00:18:20.432 --> 00:18:22.767
- Your green bean shaved ice with taro balls is here.
- He's here?

00:18:22.767 --> 00:18:22.935
-

00:18:22.935 --> 00:18:24.403
Hamaguchi Aomi!

00:18:24.403 --> 00:18:26.498
I'm going to wallop you!

00:18:29.975 --> 00:18:32.017
Hamaguchi Aomi!

00:18:33.445 --> 00:18:35.013
Hamaguchi Aomi!

00:18:35.013 --> 00:18:36.982
Yes?

00:18:36.982 --> 00:18:38.317
Welcome.

00:18:38.317 --> 00:18:41.487
Have a seat here.

00:18:41.487 --> 00:18:43.422
Please.

00:18:43.422 --> 00:18:44.784
Take a seat.

00:18:44.784 --> 00:18:46.430
All right.

00:18:48.560 --> 00:18:50.129
Charcoal toast sandwich
from Yancheng District, Kaohsiung,

00:18:50.129 --> 00:18:51.597
Squid vermicelli from Guohua Street, Tainan,

00:18:51.597 --> 00:18:53.232
Vinegar cold noodles
from Wenhua Street, Chiayi,

00:18:53.232 --> 00:18:54.466
Fried oysters from Wanggong Fishing Port.

00:18:54.466 --> 00:18:55.868
Jute leaves soup from Taichung's second market,

00:18:55.868 --> 00:18:57.102
Rolled wraps from Hsinchu's City God Temple,

00:18:57.102 --> 00:18:59.404
Pork knuckle rice
from Siping Street, New Taipei.

00:18:59.404 --> 00:19:02.046
Here, everything you wanted to eat.

00:19:02.908 --> 00:19:04.810
Are you insane? You really went to get them?

00:19:04.810 --> 00:19:07.338
I didn't buy everything.

00:19:08.113 --> 00:19:09.448
I made some.

00:19:09.448 --> 00:19:11.616
Like jute leaves soup. It was sold out.

00:19:11.616 --> 00:19:11.750
-

00:19:11.750 --> 00:19:15.754
So, I shamelessly begged
to buy the ingredients.

00:19:15.754 --> 00:19:17.823
After that, I cooked it.

00:19:17.823 --> 00:19:19.401
Eat up.

00:19:21.827 --> 00:19:24.563
Is this why you took days off?

00:19:24.563 --> 00:19:26.131
How did you know?

00:19:26.131 --> 00:19:27.900
Are you actually concerned about me?

00:19:27.900 --> 00:19:29.034
Hell no.

00:19:29.034 --> 00:19:30.869
I'm not as heartless as you.

00:19:30.869 --> 00:19:32.337
You just vanished.

00:19:32.337 --> 00:19:35.346
You went to buy stuff,
not disappear into a black hole.

00:19:35.346 --> 00:19:36.993
Sorry.

00:19:37.876 --> 00:19:39.945
I had to visit many cities.

00:19:39.945 --> 00:19:41.680
Time was tight.

00:19:41.680 --> 00:19:46.260
Most importantly, I wanted to surprise you.

00:19:47.586 --> 00:19:48.986
Go on.

00:19:51.423 --> 00:19:54.393
Does it taste good?

00:19:54.393 --> 00:19:56.328
- Delicious.
- Okay.

00:19:59.349 --> 00:20:02.582
[Jute Leaves Soup]
[I Like You]

00:20:02.582 --> 00:20:02.848
-

00:20:02.848 --> 00:20:05.883
[Fried Oysters]
[I Like You]

00:20:05.883 --> 00:20:06.188
-

00:20:14.846 --> 00:20:15.948
You...

00:20:15.948 --> 00:20:18.242
I made things hard for you on purpose.

00:20:18.242 --> 00:20:20.023
Why take it so seriously?

00:20:24.089 --> 00:20:26.424
If you need anything,
want to eat anything or drink anything,

00:20:26.424 --> 00:20:26.758
-

00:20:26.758 --> 00:20:28.693
or want to go anywhere, just ring this bell.

00:20:28.693 --> 00:20:28.819
-

00:20:28.819 --> 00:20:31.496
I'll appear right away.

00:20:31.496 --> 00:20:32.937
Here.

00:20:34.666 --> 00:20:38.868
As long as you're involved, I'll do my best.

00:20:38.868 --> 00:20:39.241
-

00:20:40.973 --> 00:20:42.908
Idiot.

00:20:42.908 --> 00:20:46.649
So, have I passed the test?

00:20:49.081 --> 00:20:50.782
What about the Heizhuyuan chicken feet,
stinky tofu from Heping Street,

00:20:50.782 --> 00:20:53.018
and garlic meat soup
from Taishan Road, Yilan?

00:20:53.018 --> 00:20:57.889
Sorry, I'll make it up to you right away.

00:20:57.889 --> 00:20:59.990
Are you crazy?

00:21:07.232 --> 00:21:08.400
Yes!

00:21:08.400 --> 00:21:09.990
What is it?

00:21:10.902 --> 00:21:13.038
Water? Coming right up!

00:21:13.038 --> 00:21:14.172
Quick, I'm dying of thirst.

00:21:14.172 --> 00:21:15.774
Okay. Sorry.

00:21:15.774 --> 00:21:17.416
Here you go.

00:21:18.710 --> 00:21:19.970
Thanks.

00:21:25.183 --> 00:21:27.286
Is any one there?

00:21:27.286 --> 00:21:28.421
Hello.

00:21:28.421 --> 00:21:30.022
- Give me a second.
- Okay.

00:21:30.022 --> 00:21:31.056
Hello.

00:21:31.056 --> 00:21:32.357
- Are you Mr. Jin?
- Yeah.

00:21:32.357 --> 00:21:33.859
Could I have your ID?

00:21:33.859 --> 00:21:35.494
Sure.

00:21:37.162 --> 00:21:40.429
Thanks. Feel free to take a look around first.

00:21:48.373 --> 00:21:50.776
Chen Hao Wei.

00:21:50.776 --> 00:21:52.044
Why are there guests?

00:21:52.044 --> 00:21:54.111
I let them in. What's wrong?

00:21:54.111 --> 00:21:54.278
-

00:21:54.278 --> 00:21:55.347
Didn't you see my note?

00:21:55.347 --> 00:21:58.216
There'll be a fishing tour coming.
We can't take in new guests.

00:21:58.216 --> 00:21:59.897
What note?

00:22:00.786 --> 00:22:02.988
- Where's my note?
- What note?

00:22:02.988 --> 00:22:04.823
My sticky note!

00:22:04.823 --> 00:22:06.224
Why isn't it here?

00:22:09.494 --> 00:22:11.197
Where did it go?

00:22:15.267 --> 00:22:17.620
Over here. It fell to the ground.

00:22:19.738 --> 00:22:21.273
Hubby, you picked such a great place.

00:22:21.273 --> 00:22:23.075
I booked it just for this.

00:22:23.075 --> 00:22:24.876
Mr. Jin, Mrs. Jin.

00:22:24.876 --> 00:22:26.378
Yes?

00:22:26.378 --> 00:22:28.847
I'm really sorry,
we had a slight miscommunication.

00:22:28.847 --> 00:22:31.550
The rooms today have been fully booked.

00:22:31.550 --> 00:22:34.586
What do you mean? So, we can't check in?

00:22:34.586 --> 00:22:36.521
- We booked a room ages ago.
- So what if you're fully booked?

00:22:36.521 --> 00:22:37.723
Yeah, you can't check in.

00:22:37.723 --> 00:22:39.391
- You can.
- But our booking was processed ages ago.

00:22:39.391 --> 00:22:41.608
You can have a room. Give me a moment.

00:22:42.594 --> 00:22:44.162
I did check with them!

00:22:44.162 --> 00:22:45.697
I called over.

00:22:45.697 --> 00:22:47.032
They said it was fine.

00:22:47.032 --> 00:22:48.700
Wait, where do we stay now?

00:22:48.700 --> 00:22:50.802
Let me contact Amicable Inn.

00:22:50.802 --> 00:22:52.804
I'm sure they have a room. Hang on.

00:22:52.804 --> 00:22:52.938
-

00:22:52.938 --> 00:22:55.107
But we want to stay here.

00:22:55.107 --> 00:22:58.076
I'm sorry, but we're full today.
[Client - Mr. Lin]]

00:22:58.076 --> 00:22:59.144
But we booked a long time ago.

00:22:59.144 --> 00:23:00.679
Hey, Madam Jiao.

00:23:00.679 --> 00:23:02.447
This is Home is He-re, I'm Xiao You.

00:23:02.447 --> 00:23:03.782
Do you have rooms available there?

00:23:03.782 --> 00:23:05.951
1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.

00:23:05.951 --> 00:23:07.920
- Great. I have guests here.
- Aren't you an elite student?

00:23:07.920 --> 00:23:08.052
-

00:23:08.052 --> 00:23:10.088
Such a lame mistake.

00:23:10.088 --> 00:23:11.390
So, you just used up Mr. Lin's money?

00:23:11.390 --> 00:23:13.125
1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.

00:23:13.125 --> 00:23:15.160
Chen Hao Wei, my money.

00:23:15.160 --> 00:23:16.795
You should be the ones taking responsibility.

00:23:16.795 --> 00:23:19.030
- We were really excited.
- We booked ages ago.

00:23:19.030 --> 00:23:20.866
- Chen Hao Wei.
- Yeah?

00:23:20.866 --> 00:23:22.000
Didn't you see my note?

00:23:22.000 --> 00:23:23.468
There'll be a fishing tour coming.
We can't take in new guests.

00:23:23.468 --> 00:23:24.603
50 centimeters straight ahead.

00:23:24.603 --> 00:23:26.405
There's a yellow sign on the left.

00:23:26.405 --> 00:23:28.612
1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.

00:23:36.548 --> 00:23:38.031
It's fine.

00:23:39.084 --> 00:23:40.886
Chen Hao Wei.

00:23:40.886 --> 00:23:41.987
Chen Hao Wei, where are you going?

00:23:41.987 --> 00:23:43.713
Chen Hao Wei, where...

00:23:49.094 --> 00:23:50.728
Chen Hao Wei!

00:24:38.610 --> 00:24:40.051
Chen Hao Wei!

00:24:41.813 --> 00:24:43.181
Chen Hao Wei!

00:24:43.181 --> 00:24:45.150
Chen Hao Wei! Stop running!

00:24:45.150 --> 00:24:47.179
Where are you running to?

00:25:00.765 --> 00:25:03.014
Chen Hao Wei!

00:25:05.203 --> 00:25:06.960
Chen Hao Wei!

00:26:13.672 --> 00:26:16.074
I'll talk to Mr. He.

00:26:16.074 --> 00:26:18.677
I'll bear the losses for this.

00:26:18.677 --> 00:26:20.145
It's fine.

00:26:20.145 --> 00:26:22.013
You didn't mean to do it.

00:26:22.013 --> 00:26:23.984
We can bear the consequences together.

00:26:26.284 --> 00:26:29.120
I'll take responsibility for my own mistakes.

00:26:29.120 --> 00:26:30.997
That's my principal.

00:26:33.705 --> 00:26:34.957
All right.

00:26:35.660 --> 00:26:38.575
You can take tomorrow off.

00:26:41.733 --> 00:26:43.456
Stop smiling.

00:26:46.050 --> 00:26:47.991
Be sad when you're sad.

00:26:48.707 --> 00:26:51.081
You don't have to smile through life.

00:26:55.914 --> 00:26:57.512
I'm really fine.

00:27:04.289 --> 00:27:05.973
Let's head to bed then.

00:27:34.452 --> 00:27:38.357
But what happened just now?

00:27:40.859 --> 00:27:42.490
Actually...

00:27:44.922 --> 00:27:46.910
I get panic attacks.

00:27:53.672 --> 00:27:56.017
You're too tensed up.

00:27:59.844 --> 00:28:03.312
It's a surprise.

00:28:03.312 --> 00:28:06.587
You're so cheerful around everyone.

00:28:07.400 --> 00:28:09.560
But you have such a huge burden.

00:28:18.963 --> 00:28:21.931
I thought my life was the worst,

00:28:23.168 --> 00:28:24.936
but after hearing you out,

00:28:24.936 --> 00:28:26.969
I think I'm pretty blessed.

00:28:31.710 --> 00:28:35.714
You know, about your issue.

00:28:35.714 --> 00:28:38.478
Is there no other solution besides medication?

00:28:39.584 --> 00:28:41.011
Running, I guess.

00:28:41.653 --> 00:28:44.634
When I run, I won't
think about all those stuff.

00:28:47.525 --> 00:28:49.664
What if you get muscle cramps?

00:28:52.864 --> 00:28:54.933
Are you even listening?

00:28:54.933 --> 00:28:57.635
I'm talking about how horrible my life is.

00:28:57.635 --> 00:29:00.338
But what are you saying?

00:29:00.338 --> 00:29:02.874
Fine, I'll share something else.

00:29:02.874 --> 00:29:05.343
You know, when I was working,

00:29:05.343 --> 00:29:09.314
I had a colleague who cried every day.

00:29:09.314 --> 00:29:12.217
I really pitied and felt bad for him.

00:29:12.217 --> 00:29:17.720
After that, I'd place tissue boxes in every corner he'd go.

00:29:17.720 --> 00:29:18.077
-

00:29:20.759 --> 00:29:22.926
- Does he have depression?
- Yeah.

00:29:22.926 --> 00:29:23.184
-

00:29:24.362 --> 00:29:27.741
But panic attacks aren't like depression.

00:29:29.000 --> 00:29:30.458
Oh, true.

00:29:31.436 --> 00:29:35.440
Listen, depression is suffering from
protracted periods of sadness.

00:29:35.440 --> 00:29:37.642
Anxiety can relapse at any moment.

00:29:37.642 --> 00:29:39.611
Get it now?

00:29:39.611 --> 00:29:41.346
Yep.

00:29:41.346 --> 00:29:44.599
So, when you see me running, don't stop me.

00:29:45.450 --> 00:29:48.307
But you almost ran into the sea today.

00:29:48.307 --> 00:29:51.324
I planned on turning back.

00:29:51.324 --> 00:29:53.026
Forget it, I regret sharing this with you.

00:29:53.026 --> 00:29:54.359
All right.

00:29:54.359 --> 00:29:56.895
We can stop talking about this.

00:29:56.895 --> 00:29:58.814
How about I tell you a joke?

00:29:59.631 --> 00:30:04.335
Do you know why campus security
is always laughing?

00:30:04.335 --> 00:30:05.670
Why?

00:30:05.670 --> 00:30:07.539
Because he's caught a funny bug.

00:30:09.974 --> 00:30:11.586
That's not funny.

00:30:12.544 --> 00:30:18.937
What will Judy get if she works too hard?

00:30:19.584 --> 00:30:21.051
Over exhaustion?

00:30:22.253 --> 00:30:24.489
A Judy good time in the hospital.

00:30:24.489 --> 00:30:26.183
I'll tell you a joke.

00:30:27.192 --> 00:30:30.328
One day, Xiao Ming and Xiao Hua
went horse riding.

00:30:30.328 --> 00:30:32.497
While they were riding,
Xiao Ming told Xiao Hua,

00:30:32.497 --> 00:30:33.918
"Hey, hold on!"

00:30:34.632 --> 00:30:36.100
After that, Xiao Hua told Xiao Ming,

00:30:36.100 --> 00:30:38.169
"Yeah, I'm holding my horses!"

00:30:38.169 --> 00:30:40.242
And then, he fell off a cliff.

00:30:42.874 --> 00:30:44.175
Look, funny, right?

00:30:44.175 --> 00:30:49.047
What will happen to penguins
if they run out of breath?

00:30:49.047 --> 00:30:50.930
Penguins running out of breath?

00:30:51.551 --> 00:30:52.616
What'll happen to them?

00:30:52.616 --> 00:30:56.554
They'll start asking, "Waddle I do?"

00:30:56.554 --> 00:30:58.089
That's such a bad joke.

00:30:58.089 --> 00:31:00.024
What do toilet papers love to do?

00:31:00.024 --> 00:31:01.759
Whose house doesn't have a telephone lines?

00:31:01.759 --> 00:31:03.194
Roll on!

00:31:03.995 --> 00:31:07.988
Seashells, because they use shell phones!

00:31:14.772 --> 00:31:16.174
He!

00:31:33.497 --> 00:31:34.947
He!

00:31:55.046 --> 00:31:56.547
Chen Hao Wei!

00:31:56.547 --> 00:31:58.671
Turn off the alarm.

00:32:02.553 --> 00:32:04.756
Sorry, it's mine.

00:32:04.756 --> 00:32:06.724
Sorry for interrupting.

00:32:06.724 --> 00:32:08.547
Have you seen Mr. He?

00:32:11.229 --> 00:32:13.898
You can't possibly have seen him
if you just woke up.

00:32:13.898 --> 00:32:15.999
- I'll look for him.
- Wait, Mr. Hua.

00:32:15.999 --> 00:32:16.200
-

00:32:16.200 --> 00:32:17.702
- Don't worry.
- It's not what you think.

00:32:17.702 --> 00:32:18.970
Old rules. I get it.

00:32:18.970 --> 00:32:20.505
It might've been too cold yesterday.

00:32:20.505 --> 00:32:21.940
Be careful.

00:32:21.940 --> 00:32:24.123
I've never been here. Bye.

00:32:33.418 --> 00:32:35.105
I'll brush my teeth first.

00:32:53.171 --> 00:32:55.840
So, you're here! I've been looking for you!

00:32:55.840 --> 00:32:57.547
Why are you so drunk?

00:33:01.479 --> 00:33:03.915
Didn't you leave the island
to look for your son?

00:33:03.915 --> 00:33:05.598
Another fight?

00:33:13.524 --> 00:33:16.794
If he knows I've made this decision,

00:33:16.794 --> 00:33:19.698
he'll come running back for a fight.

00:33:21.165 --> 00:33:22.865
What decision?

00:33:23.468 --> 00:33:24.939
Well?

00:33:28.139 --> 00:33:30.451
I'm selling the house.

00:33:34.597 --> 00:33:42.578
[Epilogue]

00:33:58.036 --> 00:33:59.570
I really suck at basketball.

00:33:59.570 --> 00:34:01.417
I always lose to you.

00:34:03.674 --> 00:34:05.543
My luck's just good this time.

00:34:05.543 --> 00:34:07.645
Maybe you'll win next time.

00:34:07.645 --> 00:34:10.815
Having fun with friends is most important.

00:34:10.815 --> 00:34:13.147
Winning and losing doesn't matter.

00:34:14.052 --> 00:34:15.668
Yeah, you're right.

00:34:17.989 --> 00:34:24.101
Besides, your hands aren't for basketball.

00:34:29.200 --> 00:34:32.604
You have Takehiko Inoue's hands.

00:34:37.642 --> 00:34:39.876
- Help me.
- Okay, hang on.

00:34:39.876 --> 00:34:40.144
-

00:34:40.144 --> 00:34:41.434
Up I go.

00:34:43.214 --> 00:34:45.059
Get up there.

00:34:50.221 --> 00:34:51.522
Chen Hao Wei.

00:34:51.522 --> 00:34:52.957
I think I forgot to grab something.

00:34:52.957 --> 00:34:54.592
What is it? I'll get it for you.

00:34:54.592 --> 00:34:56.456
It's fine, don't bother.

00:34:57.428 --> 00:34:59.864
I'll head back to get something.

00:34:59.864 --> 00:35:01.399
Caterpillars?

00:35:01.399 --> 00:35:03.367
Are you scared of caterpillars?

00:35:03.367 --> 00:35:04.569
What caterpillars?

00:35:04.569 --> 00:35:06.938
Look, cockroaches over there.

00:35:06.938 --> 00:35:08.925
Don't lie to me.

00:35:33.331 --> 00:35:34.799
5 million as compensation?

00:35:34.799 --> 00:35:35.933
Mr. President.

00:35:35.933 --> 00:35:37.668
Sorry, I'm just the manager.

00:35:37.668 --> 00:35:39.237
Photograph this dangerous building too.

00:35:39.237 --> 00:35:40.671
Let's see how we can alter it.

00:35:40.671 --> 00:35:42.206
Do you know these are ruins?

00:35:42.206 --> 00:35:44.242
I think you're really clueless.

00:35:44.242 --> 00:35:46.944
Maybe you shouldn't invest in property.

00:35:46.944 --> 00:35:48.179
I finally found you.

00:35:48.179 --> 00:35:50.147
I won't let go ever again.

00:35:50.147 --> 00:35:51.909
He Xiang Yong.